{"name":"Buddywheel","tagline":"An SVG/Javascript colourwheel. It only needs a recent browser.","body":"<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html style=\"width:800px\">\r\n   <head>\r\n        <title>Buddy Colourwheel</title>\r\n        <meta content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\" http-equiv=\"content-type\">\r\n        <meta name=\"description\" content=\"Colourwheel picker HSV\" />\r\n        <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\"/>\r\n        <meta name=\"keywords\" content=\"autobuddy,colourwheel, svg, gradient\"/>\r\n        <script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"https://github.com/frawau/BuddyWheel/js/BuddyWheel.js\"></script>\r\n        \r\n        <script type=\"text/javascript\">\r\n\r\n            window.onload = function() {\r\n                var myElt = document.getElementById(\"testme\");\r\n                var cc = colourwheel(myElt, 250, \"test-\")\r\n                cc.onchange( function(colour) {\r\n                    var myelt = document.getElementById(\"bu-fill\");\r\n                    var mycol = cc.get_hsl_colour();\r\n                    myelt.setAttribute(\"fill\",\"hsl(\"+mycol[0]+\",\"+mycol[1]+\"%, \"+mycol[2]+\"%)\");\r\n                    })\r\n                cc.set_colour([0,80,50])\r\n            };\r\n        </script>\r\n   </head>\r\n   <body>\r\n   <h1>Buddy Colourwheel</h1>\r\n   <div id=\"testme\">\r\n      <svg class=\"bu-device-icon\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" viewBox=\"0 0 1792 1792\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\">\r\n     <path class=\"bu-shape\" d=\"M1120 576q0 13-9.5 22.5t-22.5 9.5-22.5-9.5-9.5-22.5q0-46-54-71t-106-25q-13 0-22.5-9.5t-9.5-22.5 9.5-22.5 \r\n                               22.5-9.5q50 0 99.5 16t87 54 37.5 90zm160 0q0-72-34.5-134t-90-101.5-123-62-136.5-22.5-136.5 22.5-123 62-90 \r\n                               101.5-34.5 134q0 101 68 180 10 11 30.5 33t30.5 33q128 153 141 298h228q13-145 141-298 10-11 30.5-33t30.5-33q68-79\r\n                               68-180zM1400 576q0 155-103 268-45 49-74.5 87t-59.5 95.5-34 107.5q47 28 47 82 0 37-25 64 25 27 25 64 0 52-45 \r\n                               81 13 23 13 47 0 46-31.5 71t-77.5 25q-20 44-60 70t-87 26-87-26-60-70q-46 0-77.5-25t-31.5-71q0-24 13-47-45-29-45-81\r\n                               0-37 25-64-25-27-25-64 0-54 47-82-4-50-34-107.5t-59.5-95.5-74.5-87q-103-113-103-268 0-99 44.5-184.5t117-142 \r\n                               164-89 186.5-32.5 186.5 32.5 164 89 117 142 44.5 184.5z\"/>\r\n     <path id=\"bu-fill\" d=\"M1120 576q0 13-9.5 22.5t-22.5 9.5-22.5-9.5-9.5-22.5q0-46-54-71t-106-25q-13 0-22.5-9.5t-9.5-22.5 9.5-22.5 \r\n                              22.5-9.5q50 0 99.5 16t87 54 37.5 90zm160 0q0-72-34.5-134t-90-101.5-123-62-136.5-22.5-136.5 22.5-123 62-90 \r\n                              101.5-34.5 134q0 101 68 180 10 11 30.5 33t30.5 33q128 153 141 298h228q13-145 141-298 10-11 30.5-33t30.5-33q68-79 \r\n                              68-180z\" fill=\"transparent\"/>\r\n   </svg>\r\n   </div>\r\n   <h1>Introduction</h1>\r\n   <p>For a project I am working on, I needed a colourwheel. I looked around and found some on the web,\r\n   including <a href=\"http://timbaumann.info/colortriangle/\" target=\"_blank\">Colortriangle</a> (Using Canvas) and \r\n   <a href=\"http://jweir.github.io/colorwheel/\" target=\"_blank\">this colorwheel</a>. Since those guys coud not spell <em>colour</em>\r\n   and I was in a <a href=\"http://www.w3schools.com/html/html5_svg.asp\" target=\"_blank\">SVG</a> mood I decided to build my own.</p>\r\n   <p>It is pretty basic, but it works if you have a recent browser. Old browser need not apply. If you can see it at the top of this page, \r\n   your browser is OK. It does not depend on anything.</p>\r\n   <p>Usage is pretty straighforward:\r\n       <dl>\r\n            <dt>colourwheel(elt, size, prefix)</dt><dd>To create a colourwheel.<ul><li>elt: the parent DOM element,\r\n                    <li>size: the size of the colourwheel. Only one dimension is needed</li>\r\n                    <li>prefix: a string. By using a different prefix you can have more than one colourwheel.</li></ul></dd>\r\n            <vr />\r\n            <dt>set_colour(colour)</dt><dd>To set the colour of the colourwheel. the colour argumentis an array with 3 values\r\n                    <ul><li>hue; 0-360</li><li>saturation: 0-100</li><li>value: 0-100</li></ul>\r\n                    in that order.</dd>\r\n            <br />\r\n            <dt>get_colour()</dt><dd>Get the current colour. Returns an array [hue,saturation.value]</dd>\r\n            <br />\r\n            <dt>val()</dt><dd>Same as get_colour()</dd>\r\n            <br />\r\n            <dt>get_hsl_colour()</dt><dd>Get the current colour as an array with 3 values\r\n                    <ul><li>hue; 0-360</li><li>saturation: 0-100</li><li>lightness: 0-100</li></ul>\r\n                    in that order.</dd>\r\n            <br />\r\n            <dt>onchange()</dt><dd>Register a callback function. The ne parameter to that callback function is an array [hue,saturation,value]</dd>\r\n        </dl>\r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n   </body>\r\n</html>","google":"","note":"Don't delete this file! It's used internally to help with page regeneration."}